{"title":"PWR Bikes SuperBolt is an e-Balance Bike… for training, of course","link":"https://bikerumor.com/pwr-bikes-superbolt-is-an-e-balance-bike-for-training-of-course/","date":1638493557000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200224/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-0.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200224/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-0-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"PWR Bike SuperBolt e-balance bike\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200224/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-0-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200224/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-0-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200224/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-0-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200224/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-0-768x576.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200224/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-0.jpg 1400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-279880\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>If your kid has mastered a non-powered balance bike, PWR Bikes says their motorized SuperBolt will take their handling to the next level. And, honestly, it’s kinda hard to argue with that logic.</p><p>After all, many of the best mountain bikers also hone their high speed skills on motos, so, why not get them started even younger?</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200231/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200231/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-3.jpg\" alt=\"PWR Bike SuperBolt e-balance bike\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200231/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-3.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200231/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-3-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200231/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-3-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200231/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-3-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200231/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-3-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>The SuperBolt uses an 18-volt brushless motor and swappable batteries to deliver 45-70 minutes of run time depending on which speed you set it on. There are three options – Low, Mid, and Hi.</p><p>In Low Speed, young riders can get used to the assist moving them along at up to 5mph. Mid Speed bumps that to 7.5mph, and Hi Speed caps out at 11mph.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200227/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200227/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-1.jpg\" alt=\"twist throttle detail closeup on PWR Bike SuperBolt e-balance bike\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200227/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-1.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200227/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-1-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200227/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-1-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200227/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-1-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200227/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-1-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>Reining it all back in is a rear drum brake with left-hand lever, which is a bit backward for most riders. But the right-hand grip is where the throttle is, so probably best not to put too much control in a single hand for young riders who should be more focused on just learning to control the bike.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200229/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200229/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-2.jpg\" alt=\"electric motor detail closeup on PWR Bike SuperBolt e-balance bike\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200229/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-2.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200229/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-2-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200229/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-2-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200229/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-2-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02200229/pwr-bike-superbolt-electric-e-balance-bike-2-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>Specs include:</p><ul><li>18-volt brushless motor</li><li>18v 4Ah Li-Ion battery</li><li>45-70 minute run time</li><li>70-80 minute charge time</li><li>Twist grip throttle</li><li>Alloy frame</li><li>19lb 12oz w/o battery</li><li>21lb 14oz w/ battery</li><li>13.5″ standover height</li><li>16.5″ minimum saddle height</li><li>2-year frame warranty</li><li>1-year battery &amp; motor warranty</li></ul><p>The PWR SuperBolt is available now for $849, direct from their website. Oh, and this isn’t the first interesting thing we’ve covered from PWR Bike…there’s also their <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/all-wheel-drive-traction-control-propel-the-pwr-dually-e-fat-bike-over-any-terrain/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">dual-motored AWD e-Fat Bike</a> to consider.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.pwrbike.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>PWRbike.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"82ca11c12922262fec5ed1c98e349d9aa0edfe60bc345c723ac4a4b0f4c88a9a","category":"Cycling"}